to the editor statistics may seem dry to some people but they can help separate justified concern from needless worry case in point should people worry about sars severe acute respiratory syndrome a new disease now spreading worldwide philip bowring is fear spreading faster than sars op ed april 8 helped put this disease in perspective by suggesting that fear of sars may be more appropriately directed toward other more virulent diseases fear can be an appropriate motivator to learn about minimizing known risks when even experts ca n't answer important questions about a new disease caution is certainly warranted but caution should be balanced with prudence and fears should be acknowledged and placed in perspective paul mange johansen ardmore pa april 8 2003

